We first need to calculate the average owner's equity over the period. From the balance sheet we have:

• Initial Owner's Equity = Paid-in Capital + (Retained Earnings at 2023-12-31) = 13000000 + 0 = 13000000  
• Ending Owner's Equity = 10964263.48

Average Owner's Equity = (13000000 + 10964263.48) / 2  
                      = 23964263.48 / 2  
                      ≈ 11982131.74

The net profit from the income statement is –2035736.52. Using the ROE formula:

ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner's Equity) × 100  
   = (–2035736.52 / 11982131.74) × 100  
   ≈ –16.99%

Thus, the ROE is –16.99%.
